    h1 About PragueJS

    h3 Meetings
    p
    | We meet at Node5, which is open all day. If you want to talk to people before the talks start, get there at 19:00.
    | The first talk then starts at 19:00. We aim for 45 minute talks, with Q&A afterwards. We also have open discussion that can take a while longer.

    p
    | Afterwards everyone is welcome to go to pub, have a beer (or whatever beverage you prefer, and talk to attendees. In short: beer.js!

    h3 Speakers
    p
    | We're looking for two talks every month, and while some speakers come back, new speakers are always needed and welcome.
    | In general a small meetup like this is a great way to get started with doing conference talks.
    | If you're looking for some resources on getting started with public speaking, check out <a href="http://weareallaweso.me/">weareallaweso.me</a>
    p
    | If you can speak at meetup, send email to <a href="mailto:talks@praguejs.cz?subject=praguejs">administrator</a> and write topic and short description.

    h3 Sponsors
    p
    | If you are interested in supporting the Czech Javascript Meetup as a sponsor or a partner contact <a href="mailto:ladislav@prskavec.net?subject=praguejs">Ladislav Prskavec</a>.
    p
    |We need sponsors to help us bring the best JavaScript speakers to Prague. We would also appreciate help producing videos from meetups and more.

    h3 Facebook, Google Plus and Srazy.info
    p
    | We have official <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/123334754348651/">Facebook group</a> mainly in czech.
    p
    | Information about events are posted to Facebook usually at <a href="http://srazy.info/js-meetup/">Srazy.info</a> sometimes to <a href="https://plus.google.com/112099402901298502632/posts">Google Plus page</a>


    h3 Location
    p
    | Node5 is in Prague at Smichov, Radlická 50, Prague 5, Czech Republic near Metro Andel.
    ul
      li Node5 is a co-working workspace that combines the best of a business incubator and startup accelerator – mainly for early stage technology startups, programmers and graphic/UX designers.
      li If you're coming by car, tune your GPS for <a href="https://maps.google.com/maps?q=Radlick%C3%A1+50,+Prague,+Czech+Republic&hl=en&ie=UTF8&sll=37.0625,-95.677068&sspn=45.284089,91.494141&oq=Radlick%C3%A1+50,+Pr&hnear=Radlick%C3%A1+180%2F50,+150+00+Praha,+Czech+Republic&t=m&z=16">Radlická 50, Prague 5, Czech Republic</a>.
